### ============================================================
### US-TENANT-01 — View and update tenant information (landlord)
### US-TENANT-02 — Tenant account provisioning is triggered by
###                US-LEASE-01 (see leases.http). This file verifies
###                the landlord-side tenant read/update/archive flows.
### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Run in the "local" (or "device") environment from
### rest-client.env.json. The login block below captures
### @accessToken / @refreshToken for every request that follows.
### ============================================================
### ============================================================
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### capture tokens
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-TENANT-01 — List tenants derived from this landlord's leases
### Expect 200, paginated envelope { data:[...], meta:{...} }
### --------------------------------------------------------------
# @name tenantList
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###
@tenantId = {{tenantList.response.body.data[0].id}}
### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-TENANT-01 — Get a single tenant by id
### Expect 200 { data: { id, fullName, phone, email, idNumber, ... } }
### (Replace {{tenantId}} with a real id from the list above — or the
###  one returned by the lease creation in leases.http via @tenantInfoId)
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name tenantGet
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-TENANT-01 — Update approved tenant fields (landlord)
### Expect 200, returns the updated view.
### Validation: email/phone/idNumber uniqueness + format enforced.
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name tenantUpdate
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Nguyen Van A Updated",
  "phone": "0901112223",
  "email": "nguyenvana.updated@example.com",
  "idNumber": "0123456789"
}

### capture updated id for chaining
@tenantInfoId = {{tenantUpdate.response.body.data.id}}

###

### Update with a duplicate phone (expect 409 CONFLICT)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "0901112223"
}

###

### Update with an invalid email (expect 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-TENANT-01 — Soft-archive a tenant relationship
### Expect 200. Preserves lease/invoice/payment/audit history
### (soft delete → cannot be listed again; 404 if re-fetched).
### ------------------------------------------------------------
# @name tenantArchive
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-TENANT-01 — Archived tenant is no longer visible (expect 404)
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-AUTH-04 — Landlord cannot access another landlord's tenant
### (Cross-ownership uses 404 NOT_FOUND, not 403, by design.)
### Replace {{otherLandlordTenantId}} with a tenant owned by another
### landlord to confirm the 404 envelope.
### ------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/{{otherLandlordTenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ------------------------------------------------------------
### US-TENANT-02 — Tenant account is auto-provisioned on lease
### creation. To confirm: log in as the tenant (username = phone
### used in leases.http) with the emailed temporary password, then
### change it (US-AUTH-05). This is exercised end-to-end in
### leases.http (create lease → tenant login → change password).
### ------------------------------------------------------------
